<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-08T18:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-08T18:36:00-05:00" n="531" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d531">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/6754</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FHP1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-08T17:00:00-06:36">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 8, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 9, 12.85
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>552. Note of the Argentine Minister here to the Mexican Government,
                                fixing the date of the Latin-American conference of neutrals to be
                                held at Buenos Aires for the first fortnight of January next, has
                                been published with statement that Mexican Government has decided to
                                be represented thereat.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_FHP1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>